result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason L Sensabaugh was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Prosecuting attorney Andrew Herrmann in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney jeramiah maynard in court for Jason L Sensabaugh. Defendant Jason L Sensabaugh in court, in custody. The parties have a resolution and joint recommendation. Court adopts agreement. Defendant pleads guilty to Count 2. Plea is freely, knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently made. Upon motion of the State Count 1 is dismissed and read-in. Court grants motion. Defendant does not make statement. Court gives warning to deportation. Court orders the following: $500 fine plus court costs. Provide biological specimen to state crime lab for DNA analysis, and pay DNA analysis surcharge. Minutes filed.
Signed bond filed with the court.
